                <h2>Contrast</h2>
                <p>Contrast creates visual interest by highlighting differences in elements.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="emphasis">
                <h2>Emphasis</h2>
                <p>Emphasis directs attention to specific elements in the design.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="proportion">
                <h2>Proportion</h2>
                <p>Proper proportion ensures harmony and balance in the layout.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="unity">
                <h2>Unity</h2>
                <p>Unity brings together elements to create a cohesive design.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="alignment">
                <h2>Alignment</h2>
                <p>Alignment organizes elements to create a neat and structured layout.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="repetition">
                <h2>Repetition</h2>
                <p>Repetition establishes consistency and reinforces design patterns.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="whitespace">
                <h2>White Space</h2>
                <p>White space or negative space enhances readability and reduces clutter.</p>
            </section>
